Nigerian Professionals have predicted victory for Alhaji Atiku Abubakar, the Presidential aspirant of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) in the forthcoming primary election of the party. Membership of the pressure group includes but is not limited to Coordinators in America, the United Kingdom (UK), Canada and other European Countries. The National Coordinator of Nigerian Professionals for Atiku, Dr Folus Ejele who made the prediction in a Press statement in Benin City, reminded PDP that Atiku, Nigeria’s former Vice President remains the most credible aspirant that should be elected candidate of the party. -Advertisement- He assured that the Atiku project is on course by mobilizing support for Atiku ahead of the 2023 general elections. “Everything, as regards the Atiku project is on course and things, is working as planned, appealing to other Nigerians to support PDP towards a better and united Nigeria. “We are very sure and confident that 2023 will be an opportunity for us to reset Nigeria and put an end to the poverty and penury ravaging our beloved Country as we take over the helms of Affair of Government come 2023. “I enjoin all great Nigerian Professionals for Atiku to Continue their good work of ‘Atikulating, everyone, with Atikumycin’ and even add the booster dose in their sphere of influence and beyond. We remain committed to achieving the goal of securing five million Nigerian voters for the aspirant”, Ejele said.